main event: Several witnesses observed a reddish-orange object in the sky near Dauphin Island, Alabama on February 15, 1962.
interesting points: The object initially appeared round and the size of 1/3 the sun, but later changed shape to the size and shape of a football.
The object made no sound and remained stationary for a period of time before ascending vertically and disappearing.
Two additional witnesses from the 653rd Radar Squadron also observed the object, describing it as red in color, stationary, and then ascending vertically before disappearing.
The sighting occurred around dusk, shortly after sunset, when the weather was clear and cloudless.
The 93rd Radar Squadron located on Dauphin Island did not detect anything on their radar at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: A reddish-orange object that changed shape from round to football-shaped
photographs: No photographs included in the report
